column2: Migrated from EPA STORET Legacy Database- originally reported by Wisconsin DNR
Bill Burdeck said I should not monitor island lake.  This is my third reading of planting ground.
Algae present- partly cloudy- and weather right after two days of rain.
5-15 mph gusts- a storm is brewing.
Beautiful- partly cloudy.  High press day.
Partly cloudy.  Beautiful day after cold front.
Beautiful- partly cloudy- light wind- slightly more suspension solids at a very small size.  The water temperature is 74 degrees.  Lots of boaters.
Partly cloudy- the water temperature is 74 degrees- west wind at about 5 mph.  A beautiful- muggy day.
The water temperature is 75 degrees at surface.  Hot- muggy- just cleared sky from the overcast.
Slight algae (very fine)- have noticed almost complete absence of crayfish this year.
The water temperature at the surface is 67 degrees.  Higher concentration of fine- light green algae particles.  The wind is 5-7 mph and it is partly sunny.
The temperature is 60 degrees 3 feet down.  The water does not appear to have "turned" yet!  much more very small algae particles that are greenish blue in color.
Clear sky-no wind at all-4 days after 2" rainfall.
Clear-3 to 5 mph wind-have seen algal blooms floating this past week or two!
Sun subdued by high cirrus clouds- 3 mph wind- nice
Partly sunny-5 to 8 mph chop-nice day.
Partly sunny-5 to 8 mph chop-sorry forgot to mail this sooner.
High overcast- but partly sunny- 3 to 5 mph chop-algae along shores.
Partly cloudy-3 to 5 mph-a beautiful day-algae throughout.
Water level was down 3".  1' rain brought it up to normal.  Algae streaking in bays and shorelines.  Partly sunny-2 mph-62 degrees surface.
Algae on the shoreline in bags
We have not had good enough weather the past 3 weeks - 3' waves all last week - will get one more.
Partly sunny-1 mph wind n.  Water level: Up to normal high
Sunny. 3 mph. loon still on nest. lots of pollen + algae. taken with phosphorus sample.
Heavy surface algae and pollen along shoreline-full sun-5 mph-loon off nest-can't see young.  Assumed sample time was noon.
Heavy rains 4-5 days ago. third 90 F+ day in a row! water 78 F. no loon chicks survived.
Three days of rain- (2.5") ended this morning.  Temperature dropped 4 degrees- during rain period- 10-15 mph chop from w-southwest.
Partly sunny- the temperature is 62 degrees- and there is a southwest wind at 3 mph.
Surface algae in bays-4 days of 30 mph out of nw-52 degrees water.
Clear blue sky- 59.7 degrees at the surface.
72.8 F surface. Excessive pollen on surface.
73 degrees at the surface- 30-40 mph winds yesterday with a cold front moving in.
Water 72 degrees- air 72- bright sun- 5 mph.
Cold fronts and storms the last 2 weeks.
Several clear days-warm + clear-74 degree water.
Cold front came through this am.  Partly cloudy.
Gorgeous and 75 degrees.  Partly cloudy.  Wind variable at 1-3 mph.
Partly cloudy and two days after high winds.
Clear and cool.  Beautiful with no wind.
The temperature is 60 degrees- WNW winds at 15 mph and clear.
Calm-  partly cloudy-  water temperature is 54 degrees at 3 feet and 12 feet. Ice out 4/8/98.
Southwest wind at 10 mph clear. water temp. 63 degrees at 3 feet and60 degrees at12 feet.
Partly cloudy variable wind at 1-5 mph.
55 degrees partly cloudy SW wind at 2 mph.  Great fall day.  Algae on surface in bay. Green water from high fall temps.
Partly cloudy- 60 deg- NE wind 5 mph. beautiful day.

Very nice day- sunny Beautiful day- sunny.  The tamarack color is dark this year.  Darkest we have ever seen.
Per Brenton Butterfield- this sample (Sample ID 252461003) should be Planting Ground East (not west).
Per Brenton Butterfield- this sample (Sample ID 252461006) should be Planting Ground East Lobe (not west).
